output: The Sonim XP6 is a rugged smartphone designed for durability and reliability. It features a 2.63-inch IPS LCD display with a resolution of 320 x 432 pixels, protected against harsh conditions. Powered by a Qualcomm Snapdragon 400 chipset with 1GB of RAM and 8GB of internal storage, it runs on Android 4.4.2 (KitKat). The device is MIL-STD-810G compliant, IP68/IP69 rated for water and dust resistance, and can withstand drops from up to 2 meters. Equipped with a 4800mAh non-removable battery, it offers up to 40 hours of talk time and up to 1080 hours of standby time.

The Amoi M33 is a compact GSM phone announced in 2007, though it was later cancelled. It features a 1.8-inch CSTN display with a resolution of 128 x 160 pixels, offering 65K colors. The device includes 30MB of internal storage, expandable via a microSD card, and supports a phonebook with up to 500 entries. A VGA main camera is present, but there is no video recording or selfie camera. The phone is powered by a removable 700mAh Li-Ion battery and includes basic features like FM radio, MP3/MP4 playback, and SMS messaging.

The Sonim XP3400 Armor is a rugged phone designed for durability and reliability. It features a 2.0-inch TFT display with a resolution of 240 x 320 pixels, protected by Corning Gorilla Glass. The device is MIL-STD-810G compliant, IP68 dust and water-resistant, and can withstand drops from up to 2 meters. Powered by the Qualcomm QSC6085 chipset, it includes a 2 MP main camera with LED flash and supports microSDHC cards for expandable storage. The removable 1750 mAh battery provides up to 850 hours of standby time and up to 9 hours and 30 minutes of talk time.

The Blackview Shark 8 is a smartphone featuring a 6.78-inch IPS LCD display with a 120Hz refresh rate and a resolution of 1080 x 2460 pixels. It runs on Android 13 with Doke OS 4.0 and is powered by the Mediatek Helio G99 chipset, paired with 8GB of RAM and 256GB of internal storage, expandable via a dedicated microSDXC slot. The device includes a dual rear camera setup with a 64 MP main sensor and a 13 MP front-facing camera, both capable of recording high-quality video. It is equipped with a 5000 mAh battery that supports 33W wired charging. Additional features include dual SIM support, NFC, a rear-mounted fingerprint sensor, and a 3.5mm headphone jack.

The Sagem my750x is a compact mobile phone featuring a 2.4-inch TFT display with a resolution of 320 x 240 pixels. It supports GSM and HSPA networks, offering HSPA speeds of up to 3.6 Mbps. The device includes a 3.15 MP main camera with LED flash and a VGA front camera for video calls. It has a microSD card slot for expandable storage and provides essential features like SMS, MMS, and instant messaging. Powered by a removable Li-Ion battery, it offers up to 300 hours of standby time and up to 4 hours and 30 minutes of talk time.

The Telit t410 is a compact GSM phone announced in 2005 and is now discontinued. It features a TFT display with a resolution of 128 x 160 pixels and a secondary OLED display with 256 colors. The device includes a VGA main camera capable of video recording and supports SMS, EMS, and MMS messaging. It has a removable 650 mAh Li-Ion battery, offering up to 100 hours of standby time and up to 2 hours of talk time. The phone comes with 300-entry phonebook storage, downloadable polyphonic ringtones, and basic organizer tools like a video player and photo editor.

The Nokia 106 (2023) is a compact feature phone with a 1.8-inch TFT LCD display offering a resolution of 120 x 160 pixels. It supports GSM networks and comes in both single SIM and dual SIM variants, with a splash-resistant body and a built-in flashlight. The phone includes a microSDHC card slot for expandable storage, a wireless FM radio, and a 3.5mm headphone jack. Powered by a 1000 mAh Li-Ion battery, it provides essential features like SMS messaging, an MP3 player, and preloaded games. Available in Red Terracotta, Emerald Green, and Charcoal, the device is priced at approximately 80 EUR.

The Sendo S330 is a compact GSM mobile phone announced in Q4 of 2003 and is now discontinued. It features a CSTN display with 4096 colors and a resolution of 98 x 67 pixels, supporting up to 5 lines of text. The device includes a phonebook with a capacity of 500 contacts and stores up to 20 short messages, along with call records for 10 received, dialed, and missed calls. It is powered by a removable 760mAh Li-Ion battery, offering up to 480 hours of standby time and up to 7 hours of talk time. The phone supports basic messaging via SMS and EMS, has downloadable games, and includes predictive text input for convenience.

The Sonim XP8 is a rugged smartphone designed for durability and performance. It features a 5.0-inch IPS LCD display with a resolution of 1080 x 1920 pixels, protected by Corning Gorilla Glass 3. Powered by the Qualcomm Snapdragon 630 chipset and 4GB of RAM, it runs on Android 7.0 (Nougat) and offers 64GB of internal storage, expandable via microSDXC. The device is equipped with a 12 MP main camera and an 8 MP front camera, both capable of recording 1080p video. Its 4900 mAh removable battery supports 18W fast charging and provides extended usage with up to 30 hours of talk time.

The NIU Andy 3.5E2I is a compact smartphone featuring a 3.5-inch LCD display with a resolution of 320 x 480 pixels. It runs on Android 4.4 (KitKat) and is powered by a Mediatek MT6572M chipset with a dual-core 1.0 GHz Cortex-A7 CPU and 512MB of RAM. The device includes a 5 MP main camera with LED flash and panorama features, as well as a 1.3 MP front camera. It supports dual SIM functionality, offers 4GB of internal storage expandable via microSDXC, and is equipped with a 1300 mAh removable Li-Ion battery. Additional features include Wi-Fi, Bluetooth 4.0, GPS, FM radio, and a 3.5mm headphone jack.

The Cat S22 Flip is a rugged flip phone designed for durability and functionality. It features a 2.8-inch TFT LCD display with a resolution of 480 x 640 pixels, protected by Corning Gorilla Glass 5, along with a secondary external display. Powered by the Qualcomm Snapdragon 215 chipset and 2GB of RAM, it runs on Android 11 (Go edition). The device includes a 5 MP main camera with LED flash and a 2 MP selfie camera, both capable of recording video. With an IP68 rating, MIL-STD-810H compliance, and a removable 2000 mAh battery, it is built to withstand tough environments.

The BlackBerry Leap is a smartphone featuring a 5.0-inch IPS LCD display with a resolution of 720x1280 pixels, offering a 16:9 aspect ratio. It runs on BlackBerry OS 10.3.1 and is powered by a Qualcomm Snapdragon S4 Plus chipset with a dual-core 1.5 GHz processor and 2GB of RAM. The device includes 16GB of internal storage, expandable via a dedicated microSDXC slot, and is equipped with an 8 MP main camera capable of recording 1080p videos, along with a 2 MP front-facing camera. Connectivity options include Wi-Fi, Bluetooth 4.0, GPS, and microUSB 2.0, while the 2800 mAh non-removable battery provides up to 25 hours of talk time. The phone is available in black and white and was released in April 2015, though it is now discontinued.

The i-mobile 5220 is a GSM phone featuring a 2.4-inch TFT display with a resolution of 240 x 320 pixels. It includes a 5 MP main camera with autofocus and LED flash, while a selfie camera is not available. The device supports microSD cards for expandable storage and offers a phonebook capacity of up to 1000 entries with photocall functionality. Connectivity options include Bluetooth 2.0, miniUSB, and a stereo FM radio, but it lacks WLAN and GPS. Powered by a removable 1100 mAh Li-Ion battery, the phone provides up to 8 hours of talk time and up to 420 hours of standby time.

The Innostream INNO 78 is a compact GSM phone announced in 2004 and now discontinued. It features a TFT display with 256K colors and a resolution of 128 x 160 pixels, along with a second external OLED display. The device includes a VGA main camera capable of video recording and supports SMS and MMS messaging. It has a phonebook capacity of 250 entries with photo call functionality and stores up to 20 call records. Powered by a removable 650mAh Li-Ion battery, the INNO 78 also offers features like downloadable ringtones, Java support, and an organizer.

The Sony Xperia 1 III is a high-performance smartphone featuring a 6.5-inch OLED display with a resolution of 1644x3840 pixels, offering a 120Hz refresh rate and HDR support. It is powered by the Qualcomm Snapdragon 888 5G chipset, paired with 12GB of RAM and up to 512GB of internal storage, expandable via a microSDXC card. The device boasts a versatile triple-camera system with 12MP sensors, Zeiss optics, and advanced features like optical zoom and 4K video recording at up to 120fps. It runs on Android 11, upgradable to Android 13, and is equipped with a 4500mAh battery that supports 30W wired charging, wireless charging, and reverse wireless charging. The Xperia 1 III also includes IP65/IP68 water resistance, stereo speakers, a 3.5mm headphone jack, and a side-mounted fingerprint sensor.

The LeEco Le Max is a smartphone featuring a large 6.33-inch IPS LCD display with a resolution of 1440x2560 pixels, protected by Corning Gorilla Glass 3. It is powered by the Qualcomm Snapdragon 810 chipset with an octa-core CPU and 4GB of RAM, offering smooth performance. The device includes a 21 MP main camera with optical image stabilization and 4K video recording, along with a 4 MP front camera for selfies. It comes with internal storage options of 64GB or 128GB but lacks a card slot for expandable storage. The phone is equipped with a 3400 mAh non-removable battery, supports 18W fast charging, and offers additional features like a fingerprint sensor, USB Type-C, and NFC.

The Amoi E860 is a discontinued mobile device announced in 2007, featuring GSM network technology with support for GPRS. It has a 2.8-inch TFT resistive touchscreen display with a resolution of 240 x 320 pixels. The phone runs on Microsoft Windows Mobile 5.0 Phone Edition and offers 50MB of internal storage, expandable via a microSD card. It includes a 2 MP main camera capable of video recording but lacks a selfie camera. Powered by a removable 1150 mAh Li-Ion battery, the device also supports Bluetooth 1.2 with A2DP and GPS functionality using the SiRF Star III chipset.

The Posh Equal Plus X700 is a 7.0-inch tablet featuring an IPS LCD display with a resolution of 600 x 1024 pixels. It runs on Android 6.0 (Marshmallow) and is powered by a Mediatek MT8321 chipset with a quad-core 1.3 GHz Cortex-A7 CPU and 1GB of RAM. The device includes 16GB of internal storage, expandable via a microSDXC card slot, and is equipped with a 5 MP main camera and a 2 MP front-facing camera. It supports dual SIM functionality, GSM/HSPA network connectivity, and offers features like Wi-Fi, Bluetooth 4.1, GPS, and FM radio. The tablet is powered by a 2650 mAh Li-Po battery and is available in Black, Silver, and Rose Gold colors.

The Kyocera Hydro Xtrm is a compact smartphone featuring a 4.0-inch IPS LCD display with a resolution of 480x800 pixels. It is powered by a Qualcomm Snapdragon S4 Plus chipset with a dual-core 1.2 GHz processor and 1GB of RAM, running on Android 4.1.2 (Jelly Bean). The device includes a 5 MP rear camera with LED flash and a 1.3 MP front camera for basic photography needs. It is designed to be durable, offering IP57 dust and water resistance and compliance with MIL-STD-810G standards for protection against various environmental conditions. The Hydro Xtrm is equipped with a 2000 mAh removable battery, providing up to 12 hours and 30 minutes of talk time.

The Energizer E4 is a compact and lightweight mobile phone with a 1.77-inch TFT display and a resolution of 128 x 160 pixels. It supports dual SIM functionality and operates on GSM networks, with basic connectivity features like Bluetooth 2.0 and a microUSB port. The device is powered by a Unisoc SC6531DA chipset and includes 4MB of internal storage, expandable via a microSDHC card. It features a QVGA main camera with video recording capability and a 1000 mAh removable Li-Ion battery. Additional features include an FM radio, a 3.5mm headphone jack, and an SOS feature for emergencies.

The YU Ace is a smartphone featuring a 5.45-inch IPS LCD display with a resolution of 720x1440 pixels and an 18:9 aspect ratio. It is powered by a Mediatek MT6739WW chipset with a quad-core 1.5 GHz Cortex-A53 CPU and comes with either 2GB or 3GB of RAM and up to 32GB of internal storage, expandable via a dedicated microSDXC slot. The device includes a 13 MP rear camera with LED flash and a 5 MP front camera, both capable of video recording. It runs on Android 8.0 (Oreo) and is equipped with a 4000 mAh removable Li-Po battery that supports 10W wired charging. Additional features include a rear-mounted fingerprint sensor, dual SIM support, and connectivity options like Wi-Fi, Bluetooth 4.1, GPS, and FM radio.

The Nokia G310 is a 5G-enabled smartphone featuring a 6.56-inch IPS LCD display with a 90Hz refresh rate and Corning Gorilla Glass 3 protection. It runs on Android 13 and is powered by the Qualcomm Snapdragon 480+ 5G chipset, paired with 4GB of RAM and 128GB of internal storage, expandable via a dedicated microSDXC slot. The device includes a triple rear camera setup with a 50 MP main sensor, along with an 8 MP front camera, both capable of recording 1080p videos. It is equipped with a 5000 mAh battery that supports 20W wired charging and features a side-mounted fingerprint sensor for security. The phone is available in blue and is designed to be dust and splash resistant with a user-reparable QuickFix design.

The Emporia Care Plus is a compact mobile phone with a 2.2-inch TFT display and a resolution of 176 x 220 pixels. It operates on GSM technology and features a Mediatek MT6223 chipset with 4MB of RAM and 0.5MB of internal storage. The device includes a removable 1750 mAh Li-Ion battery, offering up to 300 hours of standby time and up to 6 hours of talk time. It supports basic communication features like SMS and includes Bluetooth 2.0, GPS, and an FM radio. Designed with simplicity in mind, it lacks a camera, internet connectivity, and expandable storage, making it suitable for straightforward usage.

The Modu Speedy Jacket is a compact device featuring a 1.3-inch AMOLED display with a resolution of 128x96 pixels. It operates on GSM technology and includes 1.6GB of internal storage, with support for phonebook and call records. The device is equipped with a removable 530mAh Li-Po battery, offering up to 100 hours of standby time and up to 2 hours and 30 minutes of talk time. Connectivity options include Bluetooth 1.2 and a proprietary USB port, while additional features include an MP3 player, organizer, and voice memo functionality. The Speedy Jacket is designed with a red-on-black color scheme and supports Mini-SIM cards.

The vivo T2 is a smartphone featuring a 6.62-inch AMOLED display with a 120Hz refresh rate and a resolution of 1080x2400 pixels, protected by Schott Xensation Up. It is powered by the Mediatek Helio G99 chipset paired with 8GB of RAM and 256GB of internal storage, expandable via a microSDXC card using a shared SIM slot. The device includes a triple rear camera setup with a 64MP main sensor, supported by OIS, and a 32MP front camera for selfies. It runs on Android 13 with Funtouch 13 and is equipped with a 4600mAh battery that supports 66W fast charging, capable of reaching 50% in 19 minutes. Additional features include an under-display fingerprint sensor, NFC, and dual-band Wi-Fi, with the phone available in Black Onyx, Sea Green, and Lavender Glow colors.

The ZTE nubia Red Magic 9 Pro is a high-performance smartphone designed for modern connectivity, supporting GSM, CDMA, HSPA, EVDO, LTE, and 5G networks. It features a 6.8-inch AMOLED display with 1 billion colors, a 120Hz refresh rate, and a peak brightness of 1600 nits, offering a resolution of 1116 x 2480 pixels. Powered by the Qualcomm Snapdragon 8 Gen 3 chipset and running Android 14 with Redmagic OS 9, it delivers smooth performance with up to 12GB of RAM and UFS 4.0 storage. The device includes a triple rear camera setup with a 50 MP main sensor and supports video recording up to 8K, while the 16 MP under-display selfie camera ensures a seamless design. It is equipped with a 6500 mAh battery that supports 80W wired charging and comes in multiple color options, including Black, Black/Transparent, and Silver.

The Qtek S200 is a compact device featuring a 2.8-inch TFT resistive touchscreen with a resolution of 240 x 320 pixels. It runs on Microsoft Windows Mobile 5.0 PocketPC and is powered by a 200 MHz ARM926EJ-S processor with a TI OMAP 850 chipset, paired with 64MB of RAM and 128MB of internal storage. The phone includes a 2 MP main camera capable of CIF video recording and supports connectivity options like Wi-Fi 802.11b, Bluetooth 2.0, and miniUSB. It is equipped with a removable 1200 mAh Li-Ion battery, offering up to 200 hours of standby time and up to 5 hours of talk time. The device also supports SD/MMC cards for expandable storage and features a 2.5 mm audio jack for audio output.

The Kyocera Hydro Life is a compact smartphone featuring a 4.5-inch IPS LCD display with a resolution of 540x960 pixels. It is powered by a Qualcomm Snapdragon 200 chipset with a quad-core 1.2 GHz Cortex-A7 CPU and 1.5GB of RAM, running on Android 4.3 (Jelly Bean). The device includes an 8GB internal storage, expandable via a microSDHC card slot, and a 2000mAh removable Li-Ion battery that supports up to 13 hours and 30 minutes of talk time. The Hydro Life is equipped with a 5 MP main camera with LED flash and HDR capabilities, as well as a 2 MP front camera. It is designed to be durable, offering IP57 dust and water resistance and compliance with MIL-STD-810G standards for protection against various environmental conditions.

The Toshiba Excite 13 AT335 features a large 13.3-inch LED-backlit IPS LCD display with a resolution of 1600 x 900 pixels, protected by Corning Gorilla Glass. It runs on Android 4.0 (Ice Cream Sandwich) and is powered by a quad-core 1.5 GHz Nvidia Tegra 3 chipset with 1GB of RAM. The device includes a 5 MP main camera with autofocus and LED flash, capable of recording 1080p videos, along with a 2 MP front-facing camera. It offers internal storage options of 32GB or 64GB, expandable via an SD/microSDHC card slot. The tablet is equipped with a non-removable Li-Po battery, supports Wi-Fi, Bluetooth 3.0, GPS, and includes a miniUSB 2.0 port for connectivity.

The Vertu Ascent Ti Damascus Steel is a luxury phone announced in June 2009 and released in Q3 of the same year. It features a 2.0-inch TFT display with a resolution of 240 x 320 pixels, protected by scratch-resistant glass. The device includes a 3.15 MP main camera with autofocus and LED flash but does not support video recording or a selfie camera. It offers 4GB of internal storage, supports up to 1500 phonebook entries, and does not include a card slot for expandable memory. Powered by a non-removable 950 mAh Li-Ion battery, the phone provides up to 300 hours of standby time and up to 5 hours of talk time on 2G networks.

The Unnecto Omnia is a smartphone featuring a 5.0-inch IPS LCD display with a resolution of 720 x 1280 pixels, offering a 16:9 aspect ratio. It runs on Android 5.1 (Lollipop) and is powered by a quad-core 1.0 GHz processor with a Mali-T720 GPU, paired with 1GB of RAM and 8GB of internal storage, expandable via microSDHC. The device includes an 8 MP main camera with autofocus and LED flash, capable of recording 1080p videos, along with a 3 MP front-facing camera. It supports dual SIM functionality and offers connectivity options such as 4G LTE, Wi-Fi, Bluetooth 4.0, GPS, and FM radio. The phone is equipped with a removable 2000 mAh Li-Ion battery, available in black, white, and gray color options.

The itel P40+ is a smartphone featuring a 6.8-inch IPS LCD display with a 90Hz refresh rate and a resolution of 720 x 1640 pixels. It is powered by the Unisoc T606 chipset with an octa-core CPU and comes with 4GB of RAM and 128GB of internal storage, expandable via a microSDXC card. The device includes a dual rear camera setup with a 13 MP main sensor and an 8 MP front camera for selfies, both capable of recording videos. It is equipped with a large 7000 mAh non-removable battery that supports 18W wired charging. Additional features include a side-mounted fingerprint sensor, dual SIM support, USB Type-C connectivity, and Android 12 or 13 as the operating system.

The Kyocera DuraForce is a rugged smartphone featuring a 4.5-inch IPS LCD display with a resolution of 720x1280 pixels. It is powered by a Qualcomm Snapdragon 400 chipset with a quad-core 1.4 GHz Cortex-A7 CPU and 2GB of RAM, running on Android 4.4.2 (KitKat). The device includes 16GB of internal storage, expandable via a dedicated microSDHC slot, and is equipped with an 8 MP main camera capable of 1080p video recording, along with a 2 MP front camera. Built to withstand tough conditions, it is IP68 dust/water resistant and MIL-STD-810G compliant, with a 3100 mAh non-removable battery providing up to 17 hours of talk time. Additional features include stereo speakers, NFC, GPS, and a durable design, making it suitable for demanding environments.

The Gigabyte GSmart Mika M3 features a 5.0-inch IPS LCD display with a resolution of 720 x 1280 pixels, offering a 16:9 aspect ratio. It is powered by a Mediatek MT6582 chipset with a quad-core 1.3 GHz Cortex-A7 CPU and 1GB of RAM, running on Android 4.4.2 (KitKat). The device includes a 13 MP main camera with autofocus and LED flash, as well as an 8 MP front camera for selfies. It supports dual SIM functionality and offers 8GB of internal storage, expandable via a microSDHC card. The phone is equipped with a 1900 mAh removable Li-Ion battery and includes connectivity options such as Wi-Fi, Bluetooth 3.0, GPS, and FM radio.

The Micromax In Note 1 features a 6.67-inch IPS LCD display with a resolution of 1080 x 2400 pixels, offering a 20:9 aspect ratio and oleophobic coating for added protection. It is powered by the Mediatek Helio G85 chipset with an octa-core CPU and 4GB of RAM, ensuring smooth performance. The device includes a quad-camera setup on the back, led by a 48 MP main sensor, along with a 16 MP front camera for selfies, both capable of recording 1080p videos. It houses a 5000 mAh non-removable Li-Po battery, supporting 18W wired charging and 2.5W reverse wired charging. Additional features include dual SIM support, a rear-mounted fingerprint sensor, and connectivity options like Wi-Fi, Bluetooth 5.0, and USB Type-C.

The Coolpad Cool 20 is a smartphone featuring a 6.52-inch IPS LCD display with a resolution of 720 x 1600 pixels, offering a 20:9 aspect ratio. It is powered by the Mediatek Helio G80 chipset paired with 4GB or 6GB of RAM and runs on Android 11 with CoolOS 2. The device includes a dual rear camera setup with a 48 MP main sensor and a 2 MP depth sensor, while the front houses a 5 MP selfie camera. It is equipped with a 4500 mAh non-removable Li-Po battery and supports USB Type-C with OTG functionality. Additional features include dual-band Wi-Fi, Bluetooth 5.0, and a hybrid dual SIM slot with microSDXC support.

The ZTE Blade V50 Design is a 5G smartphone featuring a 6.6-inch IPS LCD display with a 90Hz refresh rate and a resolution of 1080 x 2408 pixels. It runs on Android 13 and is powered by the Unisoc T760 chipset with an octa-core CPU and 4GB of RAM. The device includes a dual rear camera setup with a 50 MP main sensor and a 2 MP depth sensor, while the front houses an 8 MP selfie camera. It is equipped with a 4500 mAh non-removable battery that supports 22.5W wired charging. Additional features include a side-mounted fingerprint sensor, dual SIM support, NFC, and a microSDXC card slot for expandable storage.

The Gigabyte GSmart Mika MX is a dual SIM smartphone featuring a 5.0-inch IPS LCD display with a resolution of 540 x 960 pixels. It runs on Android 4.4 (KitKat) and is powered by a Qualcomm Snapdragon 410 chipset with a quad-core 1.2 GHz Cortex-A53 CPU and 1GB of RAM. The device includes 8GB of internal storage, expandable via a dedicated microSDHC slot, and is equipped with a 3000 mAh removable Li-Ion battery. For photography, it offers a 5 MP main camera with autofocus and a 2 MP front-facing camera. Connectivity options include 4G LTE, Wi-Fi, Bluetooth 4.0, GPS with GLONASS, and a microUSB 2.0 port.

The verykool s5528 Cosmo features a 5.5-inch IPS LCD display with a resolution of 720x1280 pixels, protected by scratch-resistant glass. It runs on Android 7.0 (Nougat) and is powered by a Mediatek MT6580 chipset with a quad-core 1.3 GHz Cortex-A7 CPU and 1GB of RAM. The device includes 16GB of internal storage, expandable via a microSDXC card slot. For photography, it offers an 8 MP main camera with LED flash and panorama features, as well as a 5 MP front camera. The phone is equipped with a 3000 mAh Li-Po battery, dual SIM support, and connectivity options like Wi-Fi, Bluetooth 4.0, GPS, and a microUSB 2.0 port.

The Micromax In 1b is a budget-friendly smartphone featuring a 6.52-inch IPS LCD display with a resolution of 720 x 1600 pixels. It is powered by the Mediatek Helio G35 chipset and comes with either 2GB or 4GB of RAM, paired with 32GB or 64GB of internal storage, expandable via a dedicated microSDXC slot. The device includes a dual rear camera setup with a 13 MP main sensor and a 2 MP depth sensor, while the front houses an 8 MP selfie camera. It is equipped with a large 5000 mAh non-removable battery that supports 10W wired charging and reverse wired charging. Additional features include a rear-mounted fingerprint sensor, dual SIM support, and a USB Type-C port.

The Ericsson A3618 is a GSM mobile phone announced in 2001 and is now discontinued. It features a compact design with dimensions of 111 x 47 x 22 mm and weighs 86 grams, using a Mini-SIM. The monochrome graphic display supports four background colors and includes two screensavers and start-up/shut-down animations. The phone offers a 900mAh removable NiMH battery, providing a standby time of 90-155 hours and talk time of 2.5-4 hours. Additional features include SMS messaging, three built-in games, a phonebook capacity of 99 contacts, and 10 SMS templates.

The HTC A103 is a tablet featuring a 10.1-inch IPS LCD display with a resolution of 800 x 1280 pixels, offering a 16:10 aspect ratio. It runs on Android 13 and is powered by the Mediatek MT6761B Helio A22 chipset with a quad-core 2.0 GHz Cortex-A53 CPU and 4GB of RAM. The device includes 64GB of internal storage, expandable via a microSDXC card using the shared SIM slot. For photography, it has a 5 MP main camera with LED flash and a 5 MP front camera, supporting video recording at 1080p and 720p, respectively. The tablet is equipped with a 6000 mAh non-removable Li-Po battery and supports 10W wired charging.

The TCL 40 XE is a smartphone featuring a 6.56-inch IPS LCD display with a 90Hz refresh rate and a resolution of 720 x 1612 pixels. It is powered by the MediaTek Dimensity 700 chipset, paired with 4GB of RAM and 64GB of internal storage, expandable via microSDXC. The device includes a triple rear camera setup with a 13MP main sensor, along with 2MP depth and macro lenses, and an 8MP front camera for selfies. It runs on Android 13 with TCL UI and is equipped with a 5000mAh battery that supports 18W wired charging. Additional features include 5G connectivity, a side-mounted fingerprint sensor, and a 3.5mm headphone jack.

The BenQ-Siemens E71 is a compact GSM phone with a 2.1-inch TFT display offering a resolution of 240 x 320 pixels. It features a 1.3 MP main camera capable of recording QCIF videos and supports microSD cards for expandable storage in addition to its 16MB internal memory. The device includes Bluetooth connectivity, an FM radio, and a USB 2.0 port for data transfer. Powered by a removable 730 mAh Li-Ion battery, it provides up to 390 hours of standby time and up to 6 hours and 20 minutes of talk time. The phone supports SMS, MMS, and email messaging, and comes with additional features like an MP3 player, organizer, and voice memo functionality.

The Karbonn Titanium S19 features a 5.0-inch IPS LCD display with a resolution of 720 x 1280 pixels, offering a 16:9 aspect ratio. It runs on Android 4.4.2 (KitKat) and is powered by a quad-core 1.3 GHz processor, paired with 1GB of RAM and 8GB of internal storage, expandable via a microSDHC card. The device includes a 13 MP main camera with autofocus and LED flash, along with a 5 MP front-facing camera for selfies. Connectivity options include Wi-Fi, Bluetooth 4.0, GPS, FM radio, and microUSB 2.0, while the 2000 mAh Li-Ion battery provides power. The phone supports dual SIM functionality and is available in black and white color options.

The Sharp Aquos sense5G is a compact smartphone featuring a 5.8-inch IGZO IPS LCD display with a resolution of 1080 x 2280 pixels and HDR10 support. It is powered by the Qualcomm Snapdragon 690 5G chipset, paired with 8GB of RAM and 128GB of internal storage, expandable via microSDXC. The device includes a triple rear camera setup with 12 MP wide, 8 MP telephoto, and 12 MP ultrawide lenses, capable of recording 4K videos, along with an 8 MP front camera for selfies. It is equipped with a 4570 mAh non-removable battery that supports 27W wired charging. The phone is water and dust resistant (IPX5/IP6X/IPX8) and MIL-STD-810H compliant, making it durable for various conditions.

The Parla Minu P124 is a compact dual-SIM phone with a 1.8-inch TFT display offering a resolution of 128 x 160 pixels. It features a VGA main camera capable of video recording and includes a microSDHC card slot for expandable storage. The device supports GSM networks and includes basic connectivity options like Bluetooth 2.1, microUSB 2.0, and a stereo FM radio. Powered by a removable 600 mAh Li-Ion battery, it provides up to 200 hours of standby time and up to 4 hours of talk time. The phone is available in black and white and includes essential features like a music player, video player, and organizer.

The Philips S396 is a smartphone featuring a 5.0-inch IPS LCD display with a resolution of 720 x 1280 pixels, offering a 16:9 aspect ratio. It is powered by a Mediatek MT6735P chipset with a quad-core 1.0 GHz Cortex-A53 CPU and 1GB of RAM, running on Android 5.1 (Lollipop). The device includes an 8 MP main camera with autofocus and LED flash, capable of recording 1080p videos, along with an 8 MP front camera for selfies. It supports dual SIM functionality and offers 8GB of internal storage, expandable via a dedicated microSDXC slot. The phone is equipped with a removable 2300 mAh Li-Ion battery and provides connectivity options such as Wi-Fi, Bluetooth 4.0, GPS, and FM radio.

The Oukitel WP32 is a rugged smartphone featuring a 5.93-inch IPS LCD display with a resolution of 720 x 1440 pixels. The XOLO Black 1X features a 5.0-inch IPS LCD display with a resolution of 1080 x 1920 pixels, protected by Asahi Dragontrail Glass. The Allview Soul X7 Pro is a smartphone featuring a 6.53-inch IPS LCD display with a resolution of 1080 x 2340 pixels, protected by Corning Gorilla Glass.
